title: Joey Logano corn maze recreates Daytona 500 celebration
text:
Joey Logano corn maze recreates Daytona 500 celebration 
1:41p ET Posted by Josh Richter - Shake and Bake Crew + Photo by Brian Lawdermilk/Getty Images FOX Sports Josh Richter - Shake and Bake Crew Share This Story Updated Oct 2, 2015 at 1:39p ET 
Nothing goes together quite like "Sliced Bread" and corn. 
Joey Logano received a surprise at Dover when he found out that a corn maze has been created in his honor at Schnepf Farms in Queen Creek, Arizona. Logano's post-Daytona 500 celebration was used as inspiration. Photo by Jared C. Tilton/Getty Images 
That's pretty close. There are two other corn mazes next to Logano's - one in the shape of the Shell logo and the other promoting 811, the national call before you dig phone number. 
"I was blown away by what I saw," said Logano. "The maze is incredible and I have never seen anything like before, nor would I have ever imagined being a part of something like this when I started racing. I think it's very cool that it is symbolic of our Daytona 500 win. That was a pretty big surprise and something I'll always remember. I'm pretty sure I'd get lost inside that thing."
